					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>The first three books of Maimonides' Mishneh Torah. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="233v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Mishneh Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">משנה תורה </title>
							<note>
								<p>The manuscript contains a large amount of marginal notes in Italian cursive script of apparently 16th century, refering to various authors and works. Several of these notes have been mutilated in the trimming.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="en">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204 </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="he">משה בן מימון, 1138-1204 </persName>
							</author>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">אני <name type="person" role="scribe">סעדיה בר' יוסף בן מוקאתיל</name> כתבתי ספר זה ובו מדע ואהבה וזמנים [...] וסיימתיו [...] ב<date when="1325" calendar="Hebrew">יום האחרון לחדש תמוז של שנת חמשת אלפים ופה לפרט היצירה</date> השם יזכהו וכו'.<locus n="232r"/>
							</colophon>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1v" to="27r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Introduction</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="27r" to="69r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-madaʿ </title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="69r" to="130r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ahavah</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="130r" to="232r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer hafla᾿ah</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>233 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>255</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>220</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>233 folios (+ 2 unfoliated parchment flyleaves and 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end).  </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>29 quires of 8 leaves each, numbered with Hebrew letters and marked by catchwords. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="28" writtenLines="28">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. </p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios distinguichable. </p>
									<p>Last line written outside the ruling. </p>
									<p>Many marginal notes. </p>
									<p>Chapter numbers given in larger characters. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 14th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Se῾adyah bar Yosef ben Muḳatil</name>: inscribed, folio 232r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>A contract of sale: folio 232r (the bottom of page). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yitsḥaḳ mi-Modena</name>: inscribed, folio 1v. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shelomoh ben Mosheh mi-Rimini</name>: folio 232v. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shelomoh ben Mordekhai</name>: inscribed in a deed of sale, folio 232v. The manuscript was sold by Menaḥem ben Mosheh ben Shelomoh. </p>
							<p>A record of sale in Italian and Hebrew, folio 233r ('<q>libry 116 solidy 15</q>'). </p>
							<p>A Latin note related to censorship: <q>1555 die XI dec[em]bris. Revisus p[er] d jac[obu]m Geraldini comiss[arium] ap[osto]lieum Caesar Belliossus Curiae Ep[iscopa]lis Bonon[iensis] et dicti comiss[arii] not[a]r[ius] man[da]t[us] s[ul]s[cripsit]</q>: folio 1v (bottom). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Laurentius Franguellus </name>(fl. until 1596): inscribed with his name, 1575 (folio 231v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">78</ref>, appendix § 105-110. </p>
							<p>Folio 1r and 232v contain doodles. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding contemporary="1 ">
								<p>Post-1600. Dark brown leather.  </p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Maimonides. Mishneh Torah. Hebrew. Vol. I. Brit. Mus. Additional 17,056.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
